what: ASN Brand Identity and Helper Functions
title: ASN Brand Identity and Helper Functions
text: asn package provides functions use brand identity American Society Nephrology (ASN) data visualizations made either ggplot2 highcharter. also provides helper functions: pct_chg() pct_norm() calculate percentage changes either previous values first value series pct_fun() returns summary count table vector including percentage breakdowns easily readable format get_labs() extracts label attributes object. designed pull questions column names data frame extracted haven Qualtrics SPSS .sav files select_all() counts number unique responses “Select ” questions separated across columns Qualtrics data original inspiration package came Dr. Simon Jackson’s blog post: https://drsimonj.svbtle.com/creating-corporate-colour-palettes--ggplot2. ’s highly recommended reading scale_*_asn_ramp() functions copied . However, didn’t want always use interpolated colors (created colorRampPalette) “borrowed” Matt Dancho’s approach tidyquant package, viewable https://github.com/business-science/tidyquant/blob/master/R/ggplot-scale_manual.R scale_*_asn() functions. Creation package heavily informed R Packages (2e) Hadley Wickham Jenny Bryan available https://r-pkgs.org/.

title: ASN Brand Identity and Helper Functions
text: use ASN visualizing data ggplot2:  similar application highcharter (shown)
code: library(asn) library(ggplot2)  ggplot(   iris,   aes(     x = Sepal.Length,     y = Petal.Length,     color = Species   ) ) +   geom_point() +   geom_smooth(     method = "lm",     se = FALSE   ) +   scale_color_asn(palette = "dark_mode") +   theme(     panel.background = element_rect(color = "#000000", fill = "#000000"),     plot.background = element_rect(color = "#000000", fill = "#000000"),     panel.grid = element_blank()   ) library(highcharter) library(asn)  highchart() |>    hc_add_series(     data = iris,      type = "scatter",      hcaes(       x = Sepal.Length,        y = Sepal.Width,        group = Species     )   ) |>    hc_add_theme(     asn_theme   )
